metadata.name: Electron in Trick
metadata.description:
When we sleep and then we have nightmares, perhaps caused by symptoms before we fall asleep, we do not clear our thoughts before going to sleep.  Therefore, it causes us to have nightmares or good dreams sometimes. Comparing the images in the brain, it may be thinking that there is a war of thought in the brain, so the brain thinks of ways to eliminate the war that is going on, or we call it nightmares. The images in the brain may arise from past or present memories, and most of the images are well displayed or remembered are memories of the present: 1 day has 24 hours or 1,440 minutes or 86,400 seconds, or we called the present
